Such control systems are known as stability augmentation systems (SASs).
 If the augmentation system is intended to control the mode and to provide
 the pilot with a particular type of response to the control inputs, it
 is known as a control augmentation system(CAS).
 An example of this is a normal acceleration CAS, in which the pilot’s inputs
