 which then adjust the control surfaces accordingly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Architecture of Fly-By-Wire Systems
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
An FBW system consists of the following key components:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Flight Control Computers (FCCs)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The FCCs process pilot commands, sensor inputs, and flight control laws
 to determine the required actuator movements.
 Modern FBW systems use redundant digital computers to enhance reliability.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Sensors and Feedback Systems
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
FBW systems incorporate gyroscopes, accelerometers, and other sensors to
 monitor aircraft motion and stability.
 These inputs are used to adjust control surface deflections dynamically.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Actuators
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Electronic signals from the FCCs drive electro-mechanical or electro-hydrostatic
 actuators, which move the control surfaces such as ailerons, elevators,
 and rudders.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Advantages of Fly-By-Wire Systems
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
FBW systems offer several advantages over traditional mechanical and hydraulic
 control systems: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Weight Reduction:
\series default
 Eliminates heavy mechanical linkages, reducing overall aircraft weight.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Improved Reliability:
\series default
 Redundant digital computers enhance fault tolerance and system robustness.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Enhanced Maneuverability:
\series default
 FBW allows for real-time adjustments based on sensor feedback, improving
 stability and responsiveness.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Maintenance Reduction:
\series default
 Unlike hydraulic systems, FBW does not require extensive fluid checks,
 leak management, or pressure adjustments.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Safety Features:
\series default
 Digital flight control laws can prevent dangerous maneuvers, such as stalls
 or excessive structural loads.
\end_layout

